I go to this great spot  a lot! This is the best place to have a bite.  I visit this place regularly. The food is fantastic, the staff is polite and the price is affordable. I like meeting in this place for a decent meal.

This site is my number one restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. Whenever  I I need a good lunch, this is the place that comes immediately to my mind. splendid and all sorts of  food and a large menu.helpful crew, and agreeable spirit. In addition to that, the bill is fair. I praise this place with no doubt.

Easy and tasty Chinese in FiDi. Okay -- I've only ever gotten hot and sour soup, string beans, and rice from here, but overall I find their food not gross or overly greasy. Some complaints about it being "inauthentic" in flavor here, but I think it is totally in line with Chinese-American cuisine (clearly all I ever order!) I usually pick up and eat at the office and the restaurant staff are friendly (if busy) and all looks clean in there.

This charming restaurant is located above another, its kinda hard to find, but once you do you won’t regret it. They have a great selection of food, the staff is always very friendly, and has great service highly recommended!
Nice food, quick service. Behaviour of the staff could have been better.
The customer service is regularly rapid, fantastic character, very friendly staff. I will return here again when I am nearby.
They offer a fantastic range of delicious food. I loved dining here. Staff members are always kind, pricing is convenient and the spot is always clean.
You must come.

This place was on the second floor   above another restaurant. The service was good but then again there was only two other tables eating during lunch time. The quality of the food was average. The reason for the two stars was due to my 10 minute wait as they attempted to fix the wifi and credit card machine. I would have been lenient but no communication regarding the delay led to a frustrated customer.

Staying at the Holiday Inn so decided to try this place through room service. Never again! The Wonton Soup was murky white and actually stunk when I opened it; I'll assume the shriveled blackish brown thing floating in it was the pork, selected not to try it. The Gemeral Tso's chicken was not bad per se, but it had no distinguishable flavor. The included broccoli was not cooked.  FOLLOW-UP I took the food back to which they were very apologetic and agreed to not bill the room for it.
Cancelled MealPal for the day without prior notification.

Disgusting! The whole place was dirty, every plate, every cup, every seat. The food was TERRIBLE. I ordered a Kung Pao chicken that came out and was actually old chicken re-heated with a spicy soy sauce. Waitress also ignored me and I was left with no menu for several minutes. NEVER GOING AGAIN - CLEARLY A DESPERATE TOURIST TRAP.

None of the food is authentic and the meat is even sour and bad since it's clearly they just heated up some food prepared long time ago. And they even claim it's due to they added vinegar. That's clearly a lie.
Delicious.  Will go back.

Amazing food, Comfortable atmosphere. 5 min walk from the World Trade Center. Food is made to order, so depending on traffic you may have to wait a bit. The food is WORTH it. Truly authentic Chinese cuisine in the heart of the financial district!

The meal were serviced very fast(about 5-10 minutes). So on the other hand, considering the time and price, you won't get great Chinese food. And there are not offering anything special. Still a good place for a casual meal.
Fantastic authentic Chinese food, with pleasurable service. Big portions so be aware when ordering. Would visit again if in the area.

We were after some clear soup and vegetables after indulging in so much American fast-food so ordered a simple plate of stir-fried veggies, a wonton soup and the tomato egg soup. Little did we know that it would be the most quality Chinese we’ve ever had - we’re avid travellers and have been to China so factor that in. Who knew such basic dishes could have such fine textures, flavours and freshness. Reasonable price and excellent, attentive service were a bonus.

I saw this place on yelp a couple times, but never came here until yesterday. It was a little bit difficult to find, because it is on the second floor of another restaurant. The foods are tasty,  I had sesame chicken, which was delicious, much better than Panda Express!!! Probably gonna try authentic Chinese food next time, this is a nice place to eat near WTC.

Authentic period! A little difficult to find. Go into the American Restaurant "St Georges Tavern" (Old Church), after entering, make an almost immediate left turn and go up the stairs. There you are! These folks are across the street from the Chinese museum. I think that the employees there frequent the restaurant giving importance to authentic food! Enjoy!

Came here for late lunch today. This place is surprisingly good for a high-quality Shanghai spot in downtown Wall Street area. Prices are reasonable, portions are adequate, service is fast, and food quality is consistent.
Excellent soups and dumplings.  Real Chinese food.

I typicaly won't give bad reviews but this one upset me too much. My coworkers and I went to this place last friday, simply because of the 4.1 rating of this place on google maps. We ordered some dishes, waited for 20 mins, and was told that one dish was out of stock, so we changed it to another dish. another 20 mins passed by, one dish was served, but we had to wait another 10 mins to get the forks. After that, another 10+ mins later, we were told they ran out of white rice. So we did not touch that dish at all, as we could not, and at that point, we wasted 1+ hour on a working day and we all got super upset and decided to leave. Waiter has good attitude, but sesme he was too busy with other tables. My whole point is if you go there, and see only one waiter, and there are many other people sitting already, just leave, don't waste your time.

Used to be one of my top authentic Chinese restaurants in downtown. However they changed the chef.  I used to be a huge fan and regular of this place. Last month (12/2017), I was surprised to find out that they changed the name of their restaurant and possibly the chef, because the food is horrible- tasteless at best. Very disappointed. Never been back since then.
Very attentive service! The waiter brought comforting hot water to me as soon as he saw I was pregnant. Try the wuxi ribs -- tender meat fell off bone!

It was called Tipsy Shanghai. Then the owner changed so they changed the name of the restaurant.  The food is not bad - they have some traditional dishes from the southeast China. They give free soup dumplings (minimum 10 dollar spending).  The thing I don't like now is they charge you 18% tips by default no matter how big the group is. I might pay 18% myself but it doesn't make you feel good when you are forced to do so.
